  "dependencies": [],
  "browser_support": "Modern browsers with a fine pointer; falls back to the native cursor on touch.",
  "performance_notes": "One rAF lerp loop moving the cursor toward the pointer; transform-only. Disabled on touch / coarse pointers and under reduced-motion.",
  "accessibility_notes": "The native cursor is only hidden when a fine pointer exists; keyboard users and touch are unaffected. The label is decorative — keep real, focusable controls underneath. Honor prefers-reduced-motion (no trailing).",
